  "page": "Loreon Lannister",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Loreon Lannister</b> may refer to:\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Loreon_I_Lannister\" title=\"Loreon I Lannister\">Loreon I Lannister</a>, also known as <i>Loreon the Lion</i>, first King of the Rock.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Loreon_II_Lannister\" title=\"Loreon II Lannister\">Loreon II Lannister</a>, King of the Rock.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Loreon_III_Lannister\" title=\"Loreon III Lannister\">Loreon III Lannister</a>, also known as <i>Loreon the Limp</i>, King of the Rock, son and heir of Lancel I.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Loreon_IV_Lannister\" title=\"Loreon IV Lannister\">Loreon IV Lannister</a>, also known as <i>Loreon the Lackwit</i>, King of the Rock.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Loreon_V_Lannister\" title=\"Loreon V Lannister\">Loreon V Lannister</a>, also known as <i>Queen Lorea</i>, King of the Rock, grandson of Loreon IV.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Loreon_Lannister_(son_of_Jason)\" title=\"Loreon Lannister (son of Jason)\">Loreon Lannister</a> (126 AC–?), Warden of the West, only son of Jason Lannister and Johanna Westerling.</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Loreon_Lannister&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Loren_I_Lannister\" title=\"Loren I Lannister\">Loren I Lannister</a>, also known as <i>Loren the Last</i>, last King of the Rock.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403123551\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.003 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.004 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 3/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0